{"snp5.12":{"snp5.12:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.12 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.12 ","html":"<article id='snp5.12'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.12:0.2":{"pli":"Jatukaṇṇimāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Jatukaṇṇī ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.12:1.1":{"pli":"“Sutvānahaṃ vīramakāmakāmiṃ, ","eng":"“Hearing of the hero <j>with no desire for sensual pleasures,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā jatukaṇṇi) ","eng":"said Venerable Jatukaṇṇī, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:1.3":{"pli":"Oghātigaṃ puṭṭhumakāmamāgamaṃ; ","eng":"“who has passed over the flood, I’ve come <j>with a question for that desireless one. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:1.4":{"pli":"Santipadaṃ brūhi sahajanetta, ","eng":"Tell me the state of peace, O natural visionary. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"While the exact sense of the unique term <i lang='pi' translate='no'>sahajanetta</i> is open to interpretation, surely Norman’s “omniscient one” (following Niddesa) is not right. "},"snp5.12:1.5":{"pli":"Yathātacchaṃ bhagavā brūhi metaṃ. ","eng":"Tell me this, Blessed One, as it really is. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.12:2.1":{"pli":"Bhagavā hi kāme abhibhuyya iriyati, ","eng":"For, having mastered sensual desires, <j>the Blessed One proceeds, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The following line lacks a verb, and Norman, Bodhi, and Ñāṇadīpa all construe it with <i lang='pi' translate='no'>abhibhuyya</i>: the sun “overcomes” the earth. But that doesn’t make sense. Rather, the idiom <i lang='pi' translate='no'>abhibhuyya iriyati</i> leans on <i lang='pi' translate='no'>irayati</i> in the sense “to keep going, to proceed”. The Buddha “proceeds” (i.e. keeps living) after mastering desires, like the sun “proceeds” shedding light on the earth. "},"snp5.12:2.2":{"pli":"Ādiccova pathaviṃ tejī tejasā; ","eng":"as the blazing sun shines on the earth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:2.3":{"pli":"Parittapaññassa me bhūripañña, ","eng":"May you of vast wisdom explain the teaching ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:2.4":{"pli":"Ācikkha dhammaṃ yamahaṃ vijaññaṃ; ","eng":"to me of little wisdom so that I may understand ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:2.5":{"pli":"Jātijarāya idha vippahānaṃ”. ","eng":"the giving up of rebirth and old age here.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.12:3.1":{"pli":"“Kāmesu vinaya gedhaṃ, ","eng":"“With desire for sensual pleasures dispelled,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Niddesa, followed by Bodhi, Norman, and Ñāṇadīpa, takes <i lang='pi' translate='no'>vinaya</i> as optative. But where the same phrase occurs at <a href='index.html?q=kp9#10.3'>Kp 9:10.3</a> and <a href='index.html?q=snp1.8#10.3'>Snp 1.8:10.3</a> it is clearly absolutive. Moreover, the next includes the absolutive <i lang='pi' translate='no'>daṭṭhu</i>, which elsewhere follows a similar line with an absolutive verb: <i lang='pi' translate='no'>kāmesvādīnavaṁ disvā</i>. "},"snp5.12:3.2":{"pli":"(jatukaṇṇīti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:3.3":{"pli":"Nekkhammaṃ daṭṭhu khemato; ","eng":"“seeing renunciation as sanctuary, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:3.4":{"pli":"Uggahītaṃ nirattaṃ vā, ","eng":"don’t be taking up or putting down ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"As in the Aṭṭhakavagga, it is essential that this phrase be rendered in an active present tense. It is not that nothing <em>has ever</em> been taken up or put down, but that they are no longer actively engaging in taking up and putting down. "},"snp5.12:3.5":{"pli":"Mā te vijjittha kiñcanaṃ. ","eng":"anything at all. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.12:4.1":{"pli":"Yaṃ pubbe taṃ visosehi, ","eng":"What came before, let wither away, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:4.2":{"pli":"pacchā te māhu kiñcanaṃ; ","eng":"and after, let there be nothing. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:4.3":{"pli":"Majjhe ce no gahessasi, ","eng":"If you don’t grasp at the middle, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:4.4":{"pli":"upasanto carissasi. ","eng":"you will live at peace. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.12:5.1":{"pli":"Sabbaso nāmarūpasmiṃ, ","eng":"One rid of greed, brahmin, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:5.2":{"pli":"Vītagedhassa brāhmaṇa; ","eng":"for the whole realm of name and form, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:5.3":{"pli":"Āsavāssa na vijjanti, ","eng":"has no defilements by which ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.12:5.4":{"pli":"Yehi maccuvasaṃ vaje”ti. ","eng":"they might fall under the sway of Death.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.12:5.5":{"pli":"Jatukaṇṇimāṇavapucchā ekādasamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.13":{"snp5.13:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.13 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.13 ","html":"<article id='snp5.13'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.13:0.2":{"pli":"Bhadrāvudhamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Bhadrāvudha ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.13:1.1":{"pli":"“Okañjahaṃ taṇhacchidaṃ anejaṃ, ","eng":"“I beseech you, the bastion-leaver, the craving-cutter, the imperturbable,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā bhadrāvudho) ","eng":"said Venerable Bhadrāvudha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:1.3":{"pli":"Nandiñjahaṃ oghatiṇṇaṃ vimuttaṃ; ","eng":"“the delight-leaver, the flood-crosser, the freed, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:1.4":{"pli":"Kappañjahaṃ abhiyāce sumedhaṃ, ","eng":"the formulation-leaver, the intelligent. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:1.5":{"pli":"Sutvāna nāgassa apanamissanti ito. ","eng":"Different people have gathered <j>from across the nations ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.13:2.1":{"pli":"Nānājanā janapadehi saṅgatā, ","eng":"wishing to hear your word, O hero. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:2.2":{"pli":"Tava vīra vākyaṃ abhikaṅkhamānā; ","eng":"After hearing the spiritual giant <j>they will depart from here. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:2.3":{"pli":"Tesaṃ tuvaṃ sādhu viyākarohi, ","eng":"Please, sage, answer them clearly, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:2.4":{"pli":"Tathā hi te vidito esa dhammo”. ","eng":"for truly you understand this matter.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.13:3.1":{"pli":"“Ādānataṇhaṃ vinayetha sabbaṃ, ","eng":"“Dispel all craving for attachments,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:3.2":{"pli":"(bhadrāvudhāti bhagavā ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:3.3":{"pli":"Uddhaṃ adho tiriyañcāpi majjhe; ","eng":"“above, below, all round, between. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:3.4":{"pli":"Yaṃ yañhi lokasmimupādiyanti, ","eng":"For whatever a personage grasps in the world, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:3.5":{"pli":"Teneva māro anveti jantuṃ. ","eng":"Māra pursues them right there. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.13:4.1":{"pli":"Tasmā pajānaṃ na upādiyetha, ","eng":"So let a mindful mendicant who understands ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:4.2":{"pli":"Bhikkhu sato kiñcanaṃ sabbaloke; ","eng":"not grasp anything in all the world, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.13:4.3":{"pli":"Ādānasatte iti pekkhamāno, ","eng":"observing that, in clinging to attachments, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Read (with Niddesa) as accusative plural. Norman reads <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ādānasatte</i> as locative singular, but compare the similar construction at <a href='index.html?q=thag19.1#20.3'>Thag 19.1:20.3</a>, where the former part of the line is accusative. "},"snp5.13:4.4":{"pli":"Pajaṃ imaṃ maccudheyye visattan”ti. ","eng":"these people cling to the domain of death.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.13:4.5":{"pli":"Bhadrāvudhamāṇavapucchā dvādasamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.14":{"snp5.14:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.14 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.14 ","html":"<article id='snp5.14'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.14:0.2":{"pli":"Udayamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Udaya ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.14:1.1":{"pli":"“Jhāyiṃ virajamāsīnaṃ, ","eng":"“To the meditator, rid of hopes,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā udayo) ","eng":"said Venerable Udaya, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:1.3":{"pli":"Katakiccaṃ anāsavaṃ; ","eng":"“who has completed the task, is free of defilements, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:1.4":{"pli":"Pāraguṃ sabbadhammānaṃ, ","eng":"and has gone beyond all things, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:1.5":{"pli":"Atthi pañhena āgamaṃ; ","eng":"I have come seeking with a question. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:1.6":{"pli":"Aññāvimokkhaṃ pabrūhi, ","eng":"Tell me the liberation by enlightenment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:1.7":{"pli":"Avijjāya pabhedanaṃ”. ","eng":"the smashing of ignorance.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.14:2.1":{"pli":"“Pahānaṃ kāmacchandānaṃ, ","eng":"“The giving up of both” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:2.2":{"pli":"(udayāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:2.3":{"pli":"Domanassāna cūbhayaṃ; ","eng":"“sensual desires and displeasures; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:2.4":{"pli":"Thinassa ca panūdanaṃ, ","eng":"the casting aside of dullness, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:2.5":{"pli":"Kukkuccānaṃ nivāraṇaṃ. ","eng":"and the prevention of remorse; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.14:3.1":{"pli":"Upekkhāsatisaṃsuddhaṃ, ","eng":"pure equanimity and mindfulness, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:3.2":{"pli":"dhammatakkapurejavaṃ; ","eng":"preceded by investigation of principles—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:3.3":{"pli":"Aññāvimokkhaṃ pabrūmi, ","eng":"this, I declare, is liberation by enlightenment, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:3.4":{"pli":"avijjāya pabhedanaṃ”. ","eng":"the smashing of ignorance.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.14:4.1":{"pli":"“Kiṃsu saṃyojano loko, ","eng":"“What fetters the world? ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:4.2":{"pli":"kiṃsu tassa vicāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"How does it travel about? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:4.3":{"pli":"Kissassa vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of what ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:4.4":{"pli":"nibbānaṃ iti vuccati”. ","eng":"is extinguishment spoken of?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.14:5.1":{"pli":"“Nandisaṃyojano loko, ","eng":"“Delight fetters the world. ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:5.2":{"pli":"vitakkassa vicāraṇaṃ; ","eng":"It travels about by means of thought. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:5.3":{"pli":"Taṇhāya vippahānena, ","eng":"With the giving up of craving ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:5.4":{"pli":"nibbānaṃ iti vuccati”. ","eng":"extinguishment is spoken of.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.14:6.1":{"pli":"“Kathaṃ satassa carato, ","eng":"“For one living mindfully, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:6.2":{"pli":"viññāṇaṃ uparujjhati; ","eng":"how does consciousness cease? ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:6.3":{"pli":"Bhagavantaṃ puṭṭhumāgamma, ","eng":"We’ve come to ask you, worthy sir: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:6.4":{"pli":"taṃ suṇoma vaco tava”. ","eng":"let us hear what you say.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.14:7.1":{"pli":"“Ajjhattañca bahiddhā ca, ","eng":"“Not taking pleasure in feeling ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:7.2":{"pli":"Vedanaṃ nābhinandato; ","eng":"internally and externally—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:7.3":{"pli":"Evaṃ satassa carato, ","eng":"for one living mindfully, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.14:7.4":{"pli":"Viññāṇaṃ uparujjhatī”ti. ","eng":"that’s how consciousness ceases.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.14:7.5":{"pli":"Udayamāṇavapucchā terasamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.15":{"snp5.15:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.15 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.15 ","html":"<article id='snp5.15'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.15:0.2":{"pli":"Posālamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Question of Posāla ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.15:1.1":{"pli":"“Yo atītaṃ ādisati, ","eng":"“To the one who reveals the past,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā posālo) ","eng":"said Venerable Posāla, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:1.3":{"pli":"Anejo chinnasaṃsayo; ","eng":"“who is imperturbable, with doubts cut off, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:1.4":{"pli":"Pāraguṃ sabbadhammānaṃ, ","eng":"and who has gone beyond all things, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:1.5":{"pli":"Atthi pañhena āgamaṃ. ","eng":"I have come seeking with a question. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.15:2.1":{"pli":"Vibhūtarūpasaññissa, ","eng":"Consider one who perceives that form has vanished, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"See <a href='index.html?q=snp4.11'>Snp 4.11</a>. The question refers to a meditator who has attained the dimension of nothingness. "},"snp5.15:2.2":{"pli":"sabbakāyappahāyino; ","eng":"who has entirely given up the body, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:2.3":{"pli":"Ajjhattañca bahiddhā ca, ","eng":"and who sees nothing at all ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:2.4":{"pli":"natthi kiñcīti passato; ","eng":"internally and externally. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:2.5":{"pli":"Ñāṇaṃ sakkānupucchāmi, ","eng":"I ask the Sakyan about knowledge for them; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"The Niddesa explains, in line with the Buddha’s answer, that the question is about the kind of knowledge needed to guide one with such an attainment. Thus the referent must be dative, not genitive. "},"snp5.15:2.6":{"pli":"kathaṃ neyyo tathāvidho”. ","eng":"how should that sort be guided?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.15:3.1":{"pli":"“Viññāṇaṭṭhitiyo sabbā, ","eng":"“The Realized One directly knows,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:3.2":{"pli":"(posālāti bhagavā) ","eng":"said the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:3.3":{"pli":"Abhijānaṃ tathāgato; ","eng":"“all planes of consciousness. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:3.4":{"pli":"Tiṭṭhantamenaṃ jānāti, ","eng":"And he knows this one who remains, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:3.5":{"pli":"Vimuttaṃ tapparāyaṇaṃ. ","eng":"committed to that as their final goal. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>","comm":"Read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>’dhimuttaṁ</i>; see discussion in Bodhi’s translation, note 2150. The sense is the same as eg. <a href='index.html?q=an4.125'>AN 4.125</a>. This refers to someone, such as Āḷāra Kālāma, whose spiritual goal is rebirth in the dimension of nothingness. "},"snp5.15:4.1":{"pli":"Ākiñcaññasambhavaṃ ñatvā, ","eng":"Understanding that desire for rebirth ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:4.2":{"pli":"Nandī saṃyojanaṃ iti; ","eng":"in the dimension of nothingness is a fetter, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:4.3":{"pli":"Evametaṃ abhiññāya, ","eng":"and directly knowing what this really means, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:4.4":{"pli":"Tato tattha vipassati; ","eng":"one then discerns that matter clearly. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:4.5":{"pli":"Etaṃ ñāṇaṃ tathaṃ tassa, ","eng":"That is their knowledge of truth, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.15:4.6":{"pli":"Brāhmaṇassa vusīmato”ti. ","eng":"the brahmin who has lived the life.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.15:4.7":{"pli":"Posālamāṇavapucchā cuddasamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.16":{"snp5.16:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.16 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.16 ","html":"<article id='snp5.16'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.16:0.2":{"pli":"Mogharājamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Mogharāja ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.16:1.1":{"pli":"“Dvāhaṃ sakkaṃ apucchissaṃ, ","eng":"“Twice I have asked the Sakyan,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā mogharājā) ","eng":"said Venerable Mogharāja, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:1.3":{"pli":"Na me byākāsi cakkhumā; ","eng":"“but you haven’t answered me, O Clear-eyed One. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:1.4":{"pli":"Yāvatatiyañca devīsi, ","eng":"I have heard that the divine seer ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:1.5":{"pli":"Byākarotīti me sutaṃ. ","eng":"answers when questioned a third time. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.16:2.1":{"pli":"Ayaṃ loko paro loko, ","eng":"Regarding this world, the other world, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:2.2":{"pli":"brahmaloko sadevako; ","eng":"and the realm of divinity with its gods, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:2.3":{"pli":"Diṭṭhiṃ te nābhijānāti, ","eng":"I’m not familiar with the view ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:2.4":{"pli":"gotamassa yasassino. ","eng":"of the renowned Gotama. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.16:3.1":{"pli":"Evaṃ abhikkantadassāviṃ, ","eng":"So I have come seeking with a question ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:3.2":{"pli":"atthi pañhena āgamaṃ; ","eng":"for the one of excellent vision. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:3.3":{"pli":"Kathaṃ lokaṃ avekkhantaṃ, ","eng":"How to look upon the world ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:3.4":{"pli":"maccurājā na passati”. ","eng":"so the King of Death won’t see you?” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.16:4.1":{"pli":"“Suññato lokaṃ avekkhassu, ","eng":"“Look upon the world as empty, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:4.2":{"pli":"Mogharāja sadā sato; ","eng":"Mogharāja, ever mindful. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:4.3":{"pli":"Attānudiṭṭhiṃ ūhacca, ","eng":"Having uprooted the theory of self, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:4.4":{"pli":"Evaṃ maccutaro siyā; ","eng":"you may thus cross over death. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:4.5":{"pli":"Evaṃ lokaṃ avekkhantaṃ, ","eng":"That’s how to look upon the world ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.16:4.6":{"pli":"Maccurājā na passatī”ti. ","eng":"so the King of Death won’t see you.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.16:4.7":{"pli":"Mogharājamāṇavapucchā pannarasamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.17":{"snp5.17:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.17 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.17 ","html":"<article id='snp5.17'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.17:0.2":{"pli":"Piṅgiyamāṇavapucchā ","eng":"The Questions of Piṅgiya ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.17:1.1":{"pli":"“Jiṇṇohamasmi abalo vītavaṇṇo, ","eng":"“I am old, feeble, and pallid,” ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:1.2":{"pli":"(iccāyasmā piṅgiyo) ","eng":"said Venerable Piṅgiya, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:1.3":{"pli":"Nettā na suddhā savanaṃ na phāsu; ","eng":"“my eyes unclear, my hearing faint—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:1.4":{"pli":"Māhaṃ nassaṃ momuho antarāva, ","eng":"don’t let me perish while still confused. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:1.5":{"pli":"Ācikkha dhammaṃ yamahaṃ vijaññaṃ; ","eng":"Explain the teaching so that I may understand ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:1.6":{"pli":"Jātijarāya idha vippahānaṃ”. ","eng":"the giving up of rebirth and old age here.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.17:2.1":{"pli":"“Disvāna rūpesu vihaññamāne, ","eng":"“Seeing them being harmed <j>on account of forms,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:2.2":{"pli":"(piṅgiyāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:2.3":{"pli":"Ruppanti rūpesu janā pamattā; ","eng":"“those negligent folk are inflicted <j>on account of forms—","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>","comm":"Text puns <i lang='pi' translate='no'>rupa</i> (“form”) with <i lang='pi' translate='no'>ruppati</i> (“inflicts”), as per <a href='index.html?q=sn22.79#2.1'>SN 22.79:2.1</a>. "},"snp5.17:2.4":{"pli":"Tasmā tuvaṃ piṅgiya appamatto, ","eng":"therefore, Piṅgiya, being diligent, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:2.5":{"pli":"Jahassu rūpaṃ apunabbhavāya”. ","eng":"give up form so as not to be reborn.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.17:3.1":{"pli":"“Disā catasso vidisā catasso, ","eng":"“The four quarters, the intermediate directions, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:3.2":{"pli":"Uddhaṃ adho dasa disā imāyo; ","eng":"below, and above: in these ten directions ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:3.3":{"pli":"Na tuyhaṃ adiṭṭhaṃ asutaṃ amutaṃ, ","eng":"there’s nothing at all in the world ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:3.4":{"pli":"Atho aviññātaṃ kiñcanamatthi loke; ","eng":"that you’ve not seen, heard, thought, or cognized. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:3.5":{"pli":"Ācikkha dhammaṃ yamahaṃ vijaññaṃ, ","eng":"Explain the teaching so that I may understand ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:3.6":{"pli":"Jātijarāya idha vippahānaṃ”. ","eng":"the giving up of rebirth and old age here.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.17:4.1":{"pli":"“Taṇhādhipanne manuje pekkhamāno, ","eng":"“Observing mankind sunk in craving,” ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:4.2":{"pli":"(piṅgiyāti bhagavā) ","eng":"replied the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='speaker'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:4.3":{"pli":"Santāpajāte jarasā parete; ","eng":"“tormented, mired in old age; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:4.4":{"pli":"Tasmā tuvaṃ piṅgiya appamatto, ","eng":"therefore, Piṅgiya, being diligent, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.17:4.5":{"pli":"Jahassu taṇhaṃ apunabbhavāyā”ti. ","eng":"give up craving so as not to be reborn.” ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote>"},"snp5.17:4.6":{"pli":"Piṅgiyamāṇavapucchā soḷasamā. ","html":"<p class='endsutta'>{}</p></article>"}},"snp5.18":{"snp5.18:0.1":{"pli":"Sutta Nipāta 5.18 ","eng":"Anthology of Discourses 5.18 ","html":"<article id='snp5.18'><header><ul><li class='division'>{}</li></ul>"},"snp5.18:0.2":{"pli":"Pārāyanatthutigāthā ","eng":"Homage to the Way to the Far Shore ","html":"<h1 class='sutta-title'>{}</h1></header>"},"snp5.18:1.1":{"pli":"Idamavoca bhagavā magadhesu viharanto pāsāṇake cetiye, ","eng":"This was said by the Buddha while staying in the land of the Magadhans at the Pāsāṇaka Shrine. ","html":"<p>{}"},"snp5.18:1.2":{"pli":"paricārakasoḷasānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ ajjhiṭṭho puṭṭho puṭṭho pañhaṃ byākāsi. ","eng":"When requested by the sixteen brahmin devotees, he answered their questions one by one. ","html":"{}"},"snp5.18:1.3":{"pli":"Ekamekassa cepi pañhassa atthamaññāya dhammamaññāya dhammānudhammaṃ paṭipajjeyya, gaccheyyeva jarāmaraṇassa pāraṃ. ","eng":"If you understand the meaning and the teaching of each of these questions, and practice in line with the teaching, you may go right to the far shore of old age and death. ","html":"{}"},"snp5.18:1.4":{"pli":"Pāraṅgamanīyā ime dhammāti, tasmā imassa dhammapariyāyassa pārāyananteva adhivacanaṃ. ","eng":"These teachings are said to lead to the far shore, which is why the name of this exposition of the teaching is “The Way to the Far Shore”. ","html":"{}</p>"},"snp5.18:2.1":{"pli":"Ajito tissametteyyo, ","eng":"Ajita, Tissametteyya, ","html":"<blockquote class='gatha'><p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:2.2":{"pli":"puṇṇako atha mettagū; ","eng":"Puṇṇaka and Mettagū, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:2.3":{"pli":"Dhotako upasīvo ca, ","eng":"Dhotaka and Upasiva, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:2.4":{"pli":"nando ca atha hemako. ","eng":"Nanda and then Hemaka, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.18:3.1":{"pli":"Todeyya-kappā dubhayo, ","eng":"both Todeyya and Kappa, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:3.2":{"pli":"jatukaṇṇī ca paṇḍito; ","eng":"and Jatukaṇṇī the astute, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:3.3":{"pli":"Bhadrāvudho udayo ca, ","eng":"Bhadrāvudha and Udaya, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:3.4":{"pli":"posālo cāpi brāhmaṇo; ","eng":"and the brahmin Posāla, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:3.5":{"pli":"Mogharājā ca medhāvī, ","eng":"Mogharāja the intelligent, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:3.6":{"pli":"piṅgiyo ca mahāisi. ","eng":"and Piṅgiya the great seer: ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.18:4.1":{"pli":"Ete buddhaṃ upāgacchuṃ, ","eng":"they approached the Buddha, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:4.2":{"pli":"sampannacaraṇaṃ isiṃ; ","eng":"the seer of consummate conduct. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:4.3":{"pli":"Pucchantā nipuṇe pañhe, ","eng":"Asking their subtle questions, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:4.4":{"pli":"buddhaseṭṭhaṃ upāgamuṃ. ","eng":"they came to the most excellent Buddha. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.18:5.1":{"pli":"Tesaṃ buddho pabyākāsi, ","eng":"The Buddha answered their questions ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:5.2":{"pli":"pañhe puṭṭho yathātathaṃ; ","eng":"in accordance with truth. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:5.3":{"pli":"Pañhānaṃ veyyākaraṇena, ","eng":"The sage satisfied the brahmins ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:5.4":{"pli":"tosesi brāhmaṇe muni. ","eng":"with his answers to their questions. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.18:6.1":{"pli":"Te tositā cakkhumatā, ","eng":"Those who were satisfied by the Clear-eyed One, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:6.2":{"pli":"buddhenādiccabandhunā; ","eng":"the Buddha, Kinsman of the Sun, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:6.3":{"pli":"Brahmacariyamacariṃsu, ","eng":"led the spiritual life in his presence, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:6.4":{"pli":"varapaññassa santike. ","eng":"the one of such outstanding wisdom. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.18:7.1":{"pli":"Ekamekassa pañhassa, ","eng":"If you practice in accordance ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:7.2":{"pli":"yathā buddhena desitaṃ; ","eng":"with each of these questions ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:7.3":{"pli":"Tathā yo paṭipajjeyya, ","eng":"as taught by the Buddha, ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:7.4":{"pli":"gacche pāraṃ apārato. ","eng":"you’ll go from the near shore to the far. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p>"},"snp5.18:8.1":{"pli":"Apārā pāraṃ gaccheyya, ","eng":"Developing the supreme path, ","html":"<p><span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:8.2":{"pli":"bhāvento maggamuttamaṃ; ","eng":"you’ll go from the near shore to the far. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:8.3":{"pli":"Maggo so pāraṃ gamanāya, ","eng":"This path is for going to the far shore; ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span>"},"snp5.18:8.4":{"pli":"tasmā pārāyanaṃ iti. ","eng":"that’s why it’s called “The Way to the Far Shore”. ","html":"<span class='verse-line'>{}</span></p></blockquote></article>"}}}